<br>
In no particular order:<br>
<br>
1. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wasteland</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Game that to me helped define what an RPG should be like and that they can be even better without dorfs and dragons.  It's only because Wasteland is on this list that Fallout is not.<br>
<br>
2. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sid Meier's Civilization II</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Though the first in the series was certainly more influential, I think in the second iteration it was tweaked perfectly.  The most replayable game ever.  Also of note from Sid: Alpha Centauri, Gettysburg, Railroad Tycoon and one to be mentioned below.<br>
<br>
3. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wing Commander: Privateer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
No one has yet to replicate Chris Roberts' ability to meld storytelling, space simulation and consequence-based, open-ended plots.  Though there is no game in the series which I don't think was excellent (Privateer II wasn't technically a Wing Commander game, thank gawd), Privateer's open-ended nature I don't think has been replicated in any game since.  As much as I like Earth &amp; Beyond, Privateer was a better game.  Obviously, I'm still angry and at Micro$oft for pulling the plug on Freelancer.<br>
<br>
4. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Pirates!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I played this on a Commodore 64.  I played this on a PC.  I played it on a Nintendo.  I have C-64 and Nintendo emulators on my computer just so I can still play it.  Infinite replay, minimal plot.  Along with Privateer this is the best, &quot;here's your world--now live in it,&quot; game ever produced.  Pirate and non-single-engagement-based sailing sims still haven't returned to the bar set by this game.  Also has the most playably streamlined yet strategic sailing engine I've seen.<br>
<br>
5. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Doom</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Though I'm not a big RTS-player myself, I was amazed by this game when it came out, and, of course, the RTS and Shareware revolutions really started here.  A great game.  Period.<br>
<br>
--Sslanis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubognan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bognan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/02 6:18:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3342.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top 5 games of all time</span><hr size=1> My top five would have to be:<br>
