<br>
Fort Apocalypse (Atari 800) - the most fun helicopter/flying shooter game I've ever played.<br>
<br>
Archon and Archon II (Atari 800) - Both of these games were some of Electronic Arts finest work of all time. Archon (the first one) settled many arguments between me and my brother.<br>
<br>
Secret of Monkey Island (PC) - To this day I don't think I've laughed as hard at a computer game as I did when I spent an hour trying to steal the shovel in this game. If you played this, you should know what I'm talking about.<br>
<br>
Fallout 1 &amp; 2 (PC) - These games have infinite replay value for me. The humor, the pop culture references, the reactions of the npcs, the ability to target people's groins and eyes for hand-to-hand strikes....the fun never stops.<br>
<br>
Civilization: Call To Power (PC) - I just like this one a lot better than Civ 2, or even Civ 3....<br>
<br>
Chrono Trigger (SNES) - When I bought this game on summer break from college, I think I got about 4 hours of sleep per night for 3 solid weeks trying to get every possible ending cinema.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Any thread which brings up old school computer games would not be complete for me without adding:<br>
<br>
Atari 800 &gt; C64.<br>
